Discussed with Staff
The difference between an EBI restraint and a short personal hold. When an EBI report would be needed. What constitutes a short personal hold and when, for example, a child goes to the ground it would then change to an EBI even if it was under a minute. The definition of excessive use of force and when/how to write EBI reports for each individual incident. If a Staff is ever unsure whether a situation falls into a short personal hold or EBI, they will contact the Administrator for guidance / clarification. The investigation and findings were discussed with the staff involved in this case.
The operation will conduct and all staff training on August 6th at 9AM. The all-staff training will discuss EBI and restraints. All staff will be required to sign a log to show attendance of this training. Additionally, the operation will include what was discussed and who facilitated the training. The operation has been notified a site follow up for the all-staff training will occur the week of training to obtain this record. The Administrator has confirmed they understand and will provide this. This follow up information will be noted in the HM inspection Chronology for the week of August 5th -9th week. 
