08/10/2022,748.1583(b) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/16/2022,08/16/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium Low,No,Two out of two children's files reviewed did not contain results of a TB exam and both have been placed at the facility for over 40 days.,"The following email was received from the operation as their compliance plan: 
Our process regarding intake documentation has been updated to include the use of scheduled automation to re-request any missing documentation from the state at placement. The automation will send follow-up requests at Placement, 30 days,  60 days, 90 days, and 180 days. 

If the child's health passport contains TB test information for the child the case manager will add a snapshot of this to the E Case Record and mark that as sufficient documentation and will no longer request this from the state.
If proof of TB Test is not provided at intake, or there is no date in the child's health passport, Pathfinders will utilize a walk-in clinic to administer the test and our staff RN will read and verify results within the 48-72 hour window. The results of which will be placed in the Child's E Case Record and provided to their managing conservator.
